      <body>There is still an unsolved issue with this one:
I would like:
class Post
  default_scope order(:title)
  default_scope where(:state =&gt; 'active')
end
To be similar to:
class Post
  default_scope order(:title).where(:state =&gt; 'active')
end
Since (Rails 3.0.1) activerecord-3.0.1/lib/active_record/base.rb line 890:
Thread.current[key] = Thread.current[key].presence || self.default_scoping.dup
seems to spoil stuff (.dup) I made an initializer with the following content:
class ActiveRecord::Base                                                                                                                                                                                                                     
  def self.default_scope(options = {})                                                                                                                                                                                                       
    key = :&quot;#{self}_scoped_methods&quot;                                                                                                                                                                                                          
    Thread.current[key] = nil                                                                                                                                                                                                                
    self.default_scoping &lt;&lt; construct_finder_arel(options, default_scoping.pop)                                                                                                                                                              
  end                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
end
Basically resetting Thread.current[key] when default_scope is invoked. This solves this issue, but there might be a better solution.</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;There is still an unsolved issue with this one:&lt;br&gt;
I would like:&lt;br&gt;
class Post&lt;br&gt;
default_scope order(:title) default_scope where(:state =&amp;gt;
'active') end&lt;br&gt;
To be similar to:&lt;br&gt;
class Post&lt;br&gt;
default_scope order(:title).where(:state =&amp;gt; 'active') end&lt;br&gt;
Since (Rails 3.0.1) activerecord-3.0.1/lib/active_record/base.rb
line 890:&lt;br&gt;
Thread.current[key] = Thread.current[key].presence ||
self.default_scoping.dup&lt;br&gt;
seems to spoil stuff (.dup) I made an initializer with the
following content:&lt;br&gt;
class ActiveRecord::Base&lt;br&gt;
def self.default_scope(options = {})&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
&lt;code&gt;key = :&quot;#{self}_scoped_methods&quot;
Thread.current[key] = nil                                                                                                                                                                                                                
self.default_scoping &amp;lt;&amp;lt; construct_finder_arel(options, default_scoping.pop)&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;end&lt;br&gt;
end&lt;br&gt;
Basically resetting Thread.current[key] when default_scope is
invoked. This solves this issue, but there might be a better
solution.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
